 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{1}<a_{2}<\cdots<a_{m}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{1}<b_{2}<\cdots<b_{n}$
\end_inset

 be real numbers such that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{i=1}^{m}\left|a_{i}-x\right|=\sum_{j=1}^{n}\left|b_{j}-x\right|\text{ for all }x\in\mathbb{R}.
\]

