\begin_inset Formula $a_{j}=b_{j}$
\end_inset

 for
\begin_inset Formula $1\leq j\leq n$
\end_inset

.
 To see this, note that 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(x\right):=\sum_{i=1}^{m}\lvert a_{i}-x\rvert$
\end_inset

 is not differentiable exactly on the set 
\begin_inset Formula $F:=\left\{ a_{1},\ldots,a_{n}\right\} .$
\end_inset

 This is because eacj component 
\begin_inset Formula $\lvert a_{i}-x\rvert$
\end_inset

 is non-differentiable only at 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{i}$
\end_inset

and the sum of differentiable and non-differentiable functions are not different
iable.
 Similarly, the function 
\begin_inset Formula $g\left(x\right):=\sum_{i=1}^{n}\lvert b_{i}-x\rvert$
\end_inset

 is exactly not differentiable on the set 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 which implies 
\begin_inset Formula $F=G$
\end_inset

.
