 such that for any 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\left[a,b\right]$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F\left(x\right)=F\left(a\right)+\lebInt{\lambda}{f\indicate_{\left[a,x\right]}}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
First suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 is absolutely continuous as a function.
 Then by Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:absoluteContinuityStieljesFunctions"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, the measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{F}$
\end_inset

 extended from 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{F}\left(\left(a,x\right]\right):=F\left(x\right)-F\left(a\right)$
\end_inset

 is absolutely continuous with respect to the Lebesgue measure on 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[a,b\right].$
\end_inset

 By the Radon-Nikodym theorem, there exists some 
\begin_inset Formula $f\in\mathcal{M}^{+}\left(\left[a,b\right],\borel\left(\left[a,b\right]\right)\right)$
\end_inset

 such that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mu_{F}\left(A\right)=\lebInt{\lambda}{f\indicate_{A}}
\]

\end_inset

for any 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in\borel\left(\left[a,b\right]\right).$
\end_inset

 In particular this works for 
\begin_inset Formula $A=\left[a,x\right]$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\left[a,b\right]$
\end_inset

 is a arbitrary.
 Conversely, if 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 has this integral representation then 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{F}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma\left(A\right):=\lebInt{\lambda}{f\indicate_{A}}$
\end_inset

 agree on all sets of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[a,x\right]$
\end_inset

 which means they agree on intersections of such sets which is the collection
 of all closed intervals in 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[a,b\right].$
\end_inset

 This collection is a 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi-$
\end_inset

system that generates 
\begin_inset Formula $\borel\left(\left[a,b\right]\right)$
\end_inset

 and so by Theorem 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "thm:uniquenessMeasures"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{F}=\gamma$
\end_inset

 on all Borel sets which implies absolute continuity of the measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{F}$
\end_inset

 and thus of the function 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 by the previous Proposition.
\end_layout

